, \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colin_O'Donoghue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colin_O'Donoghue\"}, {\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9999912711777028, \"rank\": 6.255476094577507e-06, \"text\": \"Sam\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"boy band\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"The Wanted\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 528}, {\"ngram\": \"Ben\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to RT\\u00c9's Evelyn O'Rourke on-stage at the Olympia, Whitmore said the play was \\\"a thriller, it's jumpy\\\", and added, it \\\"raises a lot of questions\\\".\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_O'Rourke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evelyn O'Rourke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_O'Rourke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evelyn_O'Rourke\"}, {\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999718057, \"rank\": 2.825598982524998e-11, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"stage\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"Whitmore\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"the play\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 663}, {\"ngram\": \"a thriller\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 679}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone will take something different [from it], whether you believe in ghosts or do not, you might come away feeling different,\\\" she explained.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"ghosts\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The TV star who lives in London, said it's \\\"so lovely\\\" to bring the play to Ireland as she has not \\\"been home for this long in about 15 years\\\".\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 911, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_End_theatre\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.195855176606203e-13, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_End_theatre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_End_theatre\"}, {\"begin\": 962, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999839496924, \"rank\": 1.6050266263763684e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The TV star\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 897}, {\"ngram\": \"the play\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"about 15 years\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1027}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I go home for Christmas every now and then for a week, but this is an eight-week run so it's such a fantastic opportunity,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christmas\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"a week\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"an eight-week run\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"such a fantastic opportunity\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was a bit nervous at first, probably more nervous for this more so than the West End, because it's the home crowd.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the West End\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"the home crowd\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Probably every single aunty and uncle will come to this one!\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every single aunty\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"uncle\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1322}, {\"ngram\": \"this one\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reactions have blown me away this week.\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reactions\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's quite a long stint for a play in Dublin and I am just so excited to be here and have my whole family over.\\\"\", \"from\": 1390, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1428, \"end\": 1434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5888285628776417e-15, \"text\": \"Dublin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"quite a long stint\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"a play\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"my whole family\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She added: \\\"Is not live great, it's such a special experience, and I think particularly with the Irish audience, we love a story, we are all storytellers.\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.9679238636911847, \"rank\": 0.028550265081507025, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such a special experience\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"a story\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"storytellers\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's what it is, a really good story that you get to experience with us in this one space.\\\"\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a really good story\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1701}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"this one space\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her co-star McGuiness said the Olympia theatre is \\\"perfectly designed\\\" for this play.\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Theatre,_Dublin\", \"score\": 0.5879808055174297, \"rank\": 0.6682129941389645, \"text\": \"Olympia theatre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Theatre,_Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_Theatre,_Dublin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her co\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"McGuiness\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"this play\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's so gorgeous, it looks like a chocolate box, all this design is so beautiful,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chocolate box\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"all this design\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The best thing about it, which really suits this play, is you have got these levels and people the furthest at the back are still so close, they are really on top of us.\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 2108, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The best thing\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"this play\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"these levels\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2022}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are really watching and studying, so it has a constant pressure, a really good pressure that you have to be completely natural, and not give things away, and stay in it as much as you can.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a constant pressure\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2179}, {\"ngram\": \"a really good pressure\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's perfectly designed, we are really in it together here.\\\"\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whitmore continued: \\\"And it's the history, you go into the bar and see the pictures on the walls of all the different plays and Irish legends... \\\"I grew up here, my aunty worked here her whole life, my brother worked in the Olympia, I spent so much of my childhood at gigs here, seeing plays, and now I get to perform here for eight weeks.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2497, \"end\": 2510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_mythology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irish legends\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 